Template: campsite/db_server
Type: string
Default: localhost
Description: Campsite database Server
 You must define the database server for Campsite.
 .
 If you want to configure it later, you should run 'dpkg-reconfigure campsite'.

Template: campsite/db_adm_name
Type: string
Default: root
Description: Database Administrator
 You must input the database administrator user.
 .
 If you want to configure it later, you should run 'dpkg-reconfigure campsite'.

Template: campsite/db_adm_pass
Type: string
Default: campsite
Description: Database Administrator Password
 You must input the password for the database administrator user.
 .
 If you want to configure it later, you should run 'dpkg-reconfigure campsite'.

Template: campsite/cs_db_name
Type: string
Default: campsite
Description: Campsite database Name
 You must input the Campsite database name.
 .
 If you want to configure it later, you should run 'dpkg-reconfigure campsite'.

Template: campsite/cs_db_uname
Type: string
Default: campsiteuser
Description: Campsite database User
 You must define the Campsite database user.
 .
 If you want to configure it later, you should run 'dpkg-reconfigure campsite'.

Template: campsite/cs_db_upass
Type: string
Default: camp5itE00
Description: Campsite database User Password
 You must define the Campsite database user password.
 .
 If you want to configure it later, you should run 'dpkg-reconfigure campsite'.

Template: campsite/site_url
Type: string
Default: campsite
Description: Campsite Site URL
 You must define the Campsite site URL.
 Your Campsite site would be accessed http://localhost/<siteurl>
 By default : http://localhost/campsite
 .
 If you want to configure it later, you should run 'dpkg-reconfigure campsite'.

Template: campsite/site_name
Type: string
Default: My New Campsite Site
Description: Campsite Site Name
 Enter the name/title of your Campsite site.
 .
 If you want to configure it later, you should run 'dpkg-reconfigure campsite'.

Template: campsite/site_pass
Type: string
Default: admn00
Description: Campsite Adminstration Password
 You must define the Campsite adminstration password.
 .
 If you want to configure it later, you should run 'dpkg-reconfigure campsite'.

Template: campsite/site_email
Type: string
Default: youraccount@yourdomain.org
Description: Campsite Email Address
 Enter your e-mail address, this will be the e-mail address of the site Administrator.
 .
 If you want to configure it later, you should run 'dpkg-reconfigure campsite'.

Template: campsite/site_demo
Type: boolean
Default: false
Description: Campsite templates demo
 Do you want to install the demo site ?
 .
 If you want to configure it later, you should run 'dpkg-reconfigure campsite'.

Template: campsite/webserver
Type: multiselect
Choices: apache, apache-ssl, apache-perl, apache2
Default: apache2
Description: Web server(s) that should be configured automatically:
 Choose your webserver.
 .
 If you want to configure it later, you should run 'dpkg-reconfigure campsite'.

Template: campsite/cs_db_remove
Type: boolean
Default: true
Description: Remove Database
 Do you want to remove the Campsite database ?
